    "sticky_notes": [
        {
            "id": "note_1",
            "text": "**Modifying Spreads**\nSpreads can be transformed and combined.\nHere, Euclidean rhythms (patterns of 0s\nand 1s) are scaled, reversed, and\nconcatenated into a 16-element spread\nthat drives circle radii.",
            "x": -327.2906494140625,
            "y": 32.193599700927734,
            "width": 300.0,
            "height": 120.0,
            "color": 0
        },
        {
            "id": "note_2",
            "text": "**Euclidean → Spread of 0s and 1s**\nDistributes N hits evenly across M steps.\nTwo patterns here: 5-of-8 and 3-of-8\n(with rotation=2). Each outputs an\n8-element spread.",
            "x": -100.0,
            "y": -120.0,
            "width": 300.0,
            "height": 100.0,
            "color": 1
        },
        {
            "id": "note_3",
            "text": "**PatTransform A: scale + offset**\nMaps 0/1 values to radius sizes.\n0 × 0.06 + 0.02 = 0.02 (tiny dot)\n1 × 0.06 + 0.02 = 0.08 (visible circle)\nRaw pattern becomes geometry.",
            "x": 300.0,
            "y": -120.0,
            "width": 280.0,
            "height": 100.0,
            "color": 2
        },
        {
            "id": "note_4",
            "text": "**PatTransform B: reverse + rotate**\nFlips the pattern, shifts it 2 steps,\nand uses larger scale (0.1) so hits\nbecome bigger circles (radius 0.12).\nDifferent transform = different look.",
            "x": 134.91940307617188,
            "y": 216.09228515625,
            "width": 280.0,
            "height": 100.0,
            "color": 2
        },
        {
            "id": "note_5",
            "text": "**Stack: Combining Spreads**\nConcat mode joins two 8-element spreads\ninto one 16-element spread. The first 8\nvalues come from pattern A, the next 8\nfrom pattern B.",
            "x": 550.0,
            "y": -120.0,
            "width": 280.0,
            "height": 100.0,
            "color": 1
        },
        {
            "id": "note_6",
            "text": "**Spread → Visual Mapping**\nThe 16-element stacked spread drives\nradii. Hits appear as big circles,\nmisses as tiny dots. The rhythm\nbecomes a visual pattern.",
            "x": 850.0,
            "y": -50.0,
            "width": 280.0,
            "height": 100.0,
            "color": 3
        },
        {
            "id": "note_7",
            "text": "**Try This!**\n• Change hits on either Euclidean\n• Toggle Stack mode to Interleave\n• Set probability to 0.5 on a\n  PatTransform to randomly drop hits\n• Switch render_mode to Metaball",
            "x": 1150.0,
            "y": -50.0,
            "width": 260.0,
            "height": 120.0,
            "color": 4
        }
    ]
